/ralph-loop:ralph-loop 'You are an idea generator. Your job is to append exactly ONE new idea to the file ideas.md in this repository. Each idea explores: What is the next step beyond autoresearch? Context: Ralph Loop = run an AI agent in a loop until it completes a task. Autoresearch = an AI agent autonomously modifies train.py, trains a GPT for 5 minutes, evaluates via val_bpb bits per byte, keeps improvements, discards failures, loops forever. Uses benchmarks and a fixed evaluation harness as the optimization criterion. You are brainstorming what comes AFTER this. The next evolution of autonomous AI research, optimization, and self-improving systems. INSTRUCTIONS: 1. Count how many ideas already exist in ideas.md. If the file does not exist, create it with a title. 2. The next idea number is count + 1. If count is 1000 or more, output the completion promise and stop. 3. Write exactly ONE new idea. Do NOT repeat or closely duplicate any existing idea. Skim the file first. 4. Append the idea to ideas.md in this exact format: --- then ## Idea N: Short Title then TLDR: 1-2 sentence summary then ### The Idea with 2-4 paragraphs describing the concept, what problem it solves, and why it matters then ### Implementation and Testing with how to build it, what tools/infrastructure needed, how to validate it works then ### Third-Party Perspective with an honest critical assessment. Is this useful? Does it make sense? Is it implementable with current or near-future technology? What are the risks or limitations? 5. After appending, verify the idea was written by checking the file. 6. Do NOT write more than one idea per iteration. SCOPE OF IDEAS - Think broadly: multi-agent coordination, meta-learning, curriculum design, safety, interpretability, evaluation methodology, human-AI collaboration, resource allocation, knowledge transfer, emergent capabilities, scaling laws, self-play, adversarial robustness, tool use, memory systems, reward shaping, exploration strategies, compositional generalization, etc. Ideas should be specific and concrete, not vague hand-waving. Some ideas can be incremental improvements, others can be radical paradigm shifts. Draw from ML research, systems engineering, biology, economics, game theory, or any relevant field.' \
  --max-iterations 1000 \
  --completion-promise '1000 ideas have been written to ideas.md'
